Sandoz AG said it planned a joint ventureto produce herbicides in the Soviet Union.    The company said it had signed a letter of intent with theSoviet Ministry of Fertiliser Production to form the firstforeign joint venture the ministry had undertaken since theSoviet Union allowed Western firms to enter into joint venturestwo months ago.    The ministry and Sandoz will each have a 50 pct stake, buta company spokeswoman was unable to give details of the size ofinvestment or planned output. Reuter&#3;